10/75d9d8e0-5945-11ed-baaf-c4410aa2c021" width="2000"><media:media_html><![CDATA[ ]]></media:media_html><dc:identifier><![CDATA[2]]></dc:identifier><media:credit><![CDATA[Will Lipman Photography for Engadget]]></media:credit><media:description><![CDATA[Logitech Litra Glow]]></media:description><media:title><![CDATA[Logitech Litra Glow]]></media:title></media:content></item><item><title><![CDATA[Google Photos update improves Memories view with generative AI]]></title><description type="html"><![CDATA[<p>谷歌照片<a data-i13n="cpos:1;pos:1" href="https://blog.google/products/photos/google-photos-memories-view/">刚刚进行了重大更新</a>，在其流行的记忆视图中添加了生成人工智能。该工具集已经使用您的照片和视频创建了剪贴簿蒙太奇，但现在这些蒙太奇将更加个性化，其中包含根据您的生活有意义的集合。人工智能增强算法会将图像收集到相关类别（以最近的假期为例），并创建一个吸引人的标题来配合蒙太奇。该应用程序已经或多或少地做到了这一点，但更新应该是一个根本性的改进。当然，这是人工智能，因此它并不总是能把事情做好。换句话说，您可以根据需要重命名集合或编辑蒙太奇。</p><p>所有这些剪贴簿蒙太奇现在都收集在一个名为“记忆”的专用视图中，因此您只在需要时才与它们交互。在此之前，每次有新的剪贴簿可供阅读时，Google Photos 用户都会收到推送通知。只需单击“回忆”选项卡即可开始。新选项卡还<a data-i13n="cpos:2;pos:1" href="https://www.engadget.com/google-photos-memories-redesign-sharing-163017688.html">提供对先前发布的功能的访问，</a>例如将音乐添加到剪贴簿蒙太奇以及通过应用程序分享回忆。</p><span id="end-legacy-contents"></span><p>该更新甚至允许朋友和家人共同创建这些剪贴簿条目。邀请任何人进行协作，他们可以贡献自己的照片和视频。每个参与者都可以删除任何不符合主题的照片或进行简单的编辑，系统本身会根据地理标记等推荐照片。至于更强大的共享选项，谷歌表示，您很快就可以将这些收藏保存为流行的视频格式，以便通过消息和社交媒体应用程序发送。</p><p>新的谷歌照片更新今天开始在美国推出，但该公司表示，真正的全球发布还需要几个月的时间。这并不是该公司今年第一次将生成式人工智能融入谷歌照片中。早在五月，谷歌就使用该技术<a data-i13n="cpos:3;pos:1" href="https://www.engadget.com/google-photos-will-use-generative-ai-to-straight-up-change-your-images-171014939.html">改进了其 Magic Editor 工具集，</a>该工具集利用人工智能从照片中删除不需要的伪影。</p>本文最初发表在 Engadget 上：https://www.engadget.com/google-photos-update-improves-memories-view-with-generative-ai-161749404.html?src=rss]]>; </description><link/><![CDATA[https://www.engadget.com/google-photos-update-improves-memories-view-with-generative-ai-161749404.html?src=rss]]><source_id> engadget_479</source_id><guid ispermalink="false"> 72cb638e-60e9-47c3-b956-76ff26b4ac7c</guid><dc:creator>劳伦斯·邦克</dc:creator><source/><![CDATA[Engadget]]><dc:publisher>恩杰特</dc:publisher><dc:rightsholder>恩杰特</dc:rightsholder><pubDate>Tue, 15 Aug 2023 16:17:49 +0000</pubDate><ingested> 1692119446</ingested><modified> 2023-08-15T17:10:50+00:00 </modified><category><![CDATA[Media]]></category><category><![CDATA[Technology & Electronics]]></category><category><![CDATA[Arts & Entertainment]]></category><category><![CDATA[site|engadget]]></category><category><![CDATA[provider_name|Engadget]]></category><category><![CDATA[region|US]]></category><category><![CDATA[language|en-US]]></category><category><![CDATA[author_name|Lawrence Bonk]]></category><media:content height="1194" medium="image" url="https://s.yimg.com/os/creatr-uploaded-images/2023-08/13c44b10-3b83-11ee-bfdf-bbfeaa6298b9" width="2159"><media:keywords>标题</media:keywords><media:media_html><![CDATA[ ]]></media:media_html><dc:identifier><![CDATA[1]]></dc:identifier><media:credit><![CDATA[ ]]></media:credit><media:description><![CDATA[ ]]></media:description><media:title><![CDATA[ ]]></media:title></media:content><media:content height="1194" medium="image" url="https://media-mbst-pub-ue1.s3.amazonaws.com/creatr-uploaded-images/2023-08/13c44b10-3b83-11ee-bfdf-bbfeaa6298b9" width="2159"><media:media_html><![CDATA[ ]]></media:media_html><dc:identifier><![CDATA[2]]></dc:identifier><media:credit><![CDATA[Google]]></media:credit><media:description><![CDATA[View of Google Photos app.]]></media:description><media:title><![CDATA[Google Photos AI]]></media:title></media:content></item><item><title><![CDATA[The best gaming mouse in 2023]]></title><description type="html"><![CDATA[<p>如果您经常在电脑上玩游戏，好的鼠标可以让您更好地控制光标，添加更多按钮，您可以根据自己的喜好进行自定义，通常会让您的休息时间更加舒适。在竞技游戏中，最好的游戏鼠标不会神奇地让你势不可挡，但更快的响应时间和额外的输入应该会带来更愉快和反应灵敏的体验。</p><p>最适合您的游戏鼠标最终取决于您的偏好——它的形状是否适合您的手以及其功能集是否适合您的特定游戏需求。不过，在过去的几个月里，我们开始寻找一些可能符合要求的 PC 游戏选项，无论是 FPS、MMO 还是介于两者之间的任何游戏。在研究了数十只鼠标、测试了大约 20 只鼠标并玩了无数小时的《<em>守望先锋</em>》、 <em>《反恐精英：全球攻势》</em> 、 <em>《光环无限》</em>和<em>《最终幻想 XIV</em> 》（以及其他游戏）后，我们发现了以下内容，并附上了一些一般性的购买建议。</p><span id="end-legacy-contents"></span><h2>购买游戏鼠标需要注意什么</h2><h3>有线与无线</h3><p>过去购买无线游戏鼠标意味着牺牲一定程度的响应能力，但值得庆幸的是，现在情况已不再如此。在过去的几年中，无线连接已经改进到了良好的无线模型和经过验证的有线游戏鼠标之间的延迟差异几乎难以察觉的程度。</p><p>但请注意，我们严格讨论的是使用 2.4GHz 连接（通过 USB 适配器）的鼠标，而不是蓝牙。许多无线型号都支持这两种连接选项，这非常适合旅行，但蓝牙的延迟通常太高，无法可靠地玩游戏。</p><p>无线化还需要权衡其他因素。电池寿命一直在提高，但由于其更高的性能要求和 RGB 照明，大多数无线游戏鼠标的使用寿命通常不如“普通”无线型号那么长。您不应该期望经常使用的可充电游戏鼠标的电量能够持续几天。好的无线游戏鼠标的成本通常也比有线游戏鼠标高得多。</p><p>这并不是说溢价永远不值得：谁想要在办公桌上再多<em>一根</em>电缆？如果您讨厌“电缆拖拽”的感觉或者您的游戏电脑位于一个尴尬的位置，您可能需要无线型号。许多无线游戏鼠标都配有电缆，您也可以在紧要关头连接起来。但如果价格是任何问题的话，好的有线鼠标通常更有价值。</p><h3>舒适度和抓地力类型</h3><p>每个人的手都不同，所以归根结底，称一只鼠标比另一只“更舒服”大多是主观的。不过，在购买任何鼠标时，确保您的舒适度是最重要的一步，因此我们已尽力考虑我们测试的每款设备如何在小手、中等尺寸和大手上使用。</p><p>我们还考虑了每种设备如何适应大多数人握持鼠标时使用的三种抓握方式：手掌、指尖和爪子。回顾一下，手掌握持是指您的整只手放在鼠标上，手指平放在主要按钮上。指尖握持是指仅用指尖操控鼠标，手掌完全不与设备接触。爪式抓握是指您的手掌仅接触鼠标的后边缘，手指呈爪状拱向按钮。</p><p>一般来说，大多数人使用手掌握持，这往往提供最好的控制感 - 不过，根据您的手的大小，您可能需要将鼠标设置为特定长度才能舒适地使用它。指尖握持可以实现更快速的移动，而爪握则可以在两者之间取得平衡。如果您想了解更多详细信息<a data-i13n="cpos:1;pos:1" href="https://switchandclick.com/mouse-grips/">，“切换和单击”</a>有一个很好的细分，但如果鼠标不太适合特定的握持方式，我们会在下面注明。无论如何，大多数时候你的确实是一个爪式抓手。</p><h3>打造品质和设计</h3><p>好的游戏鼠标感觉坚固，在剧烈使用时不会弯曲或发出吱吱声。我们重视没有任何过于尖锐的角度或凹槽的鼠标，这些角度或凹槽对于大多数人来说可能会很尴尬。虽然大多数游戏鼠标都有塑料外壳，但并非所有塑料都是一样的，因此我们寻找光滑、不太光滑且能够承受竞技游戏过程中经常出现的手掌出汗的表面处理。</p><p>游戏鼠标市场主要分为两种设计风格：人体工程学和双手灵巧。符合人体工程学的游戏鼠标几乎总是考虑到惯用右手的用户，并且通常具有专用的拇指托。双手灵巧的鼠标更加对称，设计为可以用任意一只手使用（尽管它们两侧可能没有额外的按钮）。哪种形状最适合您很大程度上取决于个人喜好。</p><p>与此同时，游戏鼠标的脚应该提供一致的滑动，并尽可能减少鼠标与其下方表面之间的摩擦。为了获得最佳性能，请寻找由<a data-i13n="cpos:2;pos:1" href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Polytetrafluoroethylene">PTFE</a> （又名特氟龙）制成的脚。所有脚最终都会磨损，但许多鼠标都配有备件，并且大多数制造商会在需要时出售替换件。</p><p>至于华丽的 RGB 灯光，这是一个不错的奖励，但仅此而已。不过，如果您已经为您的设置配备了 RGB，那么拥有可调节灯光效果的鼠标可以增加游戏体验（并且更多的消费技术可以为了快乐而做事）。更实际的是，某些鼠标允许您将自定义照明设置分配给单独的配置文件，这可以让您更轻松地查看您当前正在使用哪一个。</p><h3>重量</h3><p>近年来，游戏鼠标变得越来越轻，我们测试的一些型号的重量仅为 45 克。您的鼠标<em>不需要</em>那么轻 - 任何低于 80 克的鼠标仍然相当轻，而且它不像 100 克鼠标那样感觉像锚。无论如何，较轻的重量可以更轻松地完成重复的快速运动，并且惯性较小。也就是说，一些玩家仍然喜欢游戏鼠标的体积大一点（相对而言），尤其是那些不那么依赖抽搐反应的游戏。</p><p>为了减轻重量，一些制造商推出了采用“蜂窝”式设计的游戏鼠标，其外壳上有多个切口。这些鼠标仍然可以表现出色，但是有一堆孔使内部电路板暴露在可能的汗水、灰尘和碎屑中，这对于长期耐用性来说并不是最好的。因此，我们通常会避免推荐采用这种设计的型号。</p><h3>开关、按钮和滚轮</h3><p>越来越多的游戏鼠标使用光学开关而不是机械开关。由于这些涉及进行物理接触的部件较少，因此它们通常应该更耐用，并且随着时间的推移，不太容易出现不必要的“双击”。带有机械开关的小鼠仍然有很多优点，但它们在真空中承担着更多的长期风险。</p><p>由于大多数人都会将游戏<em>鼠标</em>用作鼠标，因此我们看重主按钮按下时感觉较柔和的型号，并且有足够的行程以减少意外启动的频率。但即便如此，这也是一个偏好问题：如果您玩需要持续点击的游戏，您可能需要更轻的按钮。此外，我们还通过<a data-i13n="cpos:3;pos:1" href="https://www.rtings.com/mouse/tests/control/latency">Rtings 等网站</a>进行测试，以确保我们推荐的每款鼠标都具有足够低的点击延迟，这意味着您的点击将以最小的延迟进行注册。</p><p>除了标准的点击面板之外，好的游戏鼠标还应该具有用于​​快速宏或快捷方式的可编程按钮。对于大多数游戏，请在拇指侧至少找到两个额外的按钮，这些按钮易于触及且不易意外按下。 Lots of mice have more buttons, which can be a plus, but not if they force you to contort your fingers to avoid hitting them. For MMO mice, having at least 12 side buttons is preferable in order to access as many hotbar commands as possible.</p><p> As for the scroll wheel, it should have distinct, ratcheted “steps” that aren&#39;t too resistant but make it clear when you&#39;ve actually scrolled. Its texture should be grippy, and it shouldn&#39;t make a distracting amount of noise when used. The wheel should also be clickable, giving you another input to customize for certain games (eg, to control the zoom on a sniper rifle).</p><h3> Sensors and performance</h3><p> Some are more proficient than others, but generally speaking, the optical sensors built into most modern gaming mice are more than fast and accurate enough for most people&#39;s needs.</p><p> While shopping for gaming mice, you&#39;ll see a number of terms related to sensor performance. To be clear, a gaming mouse&#39;s responsiveness doesn&#39;t come down to just one spec. But for clarity&#39;s sake, here&#39;s a rundown of the more noteworthy jargon:</p><ul><li><p> DPI, or dots per inch, is a measure of a mouse&#39;s sensitivity. The higher the DPI setting, the more your cursor will move with every inch you move the mouse itself. Many of the best gaming mice advertise extremely high DPIs that top out above 20,000 or 30,000, but that&#39;s largely marketing fluff: Few people play above 3,000, with 800 a common sweet spot. This concept is also referred to as CPI (counts per inch), which <a data-i13n="cpos:4;pos:1" href="https://www.pcgamer.com/DPI-vs-CPI/">is probably</a> the more accurate term, though DPI is used more often.</p></li><li><p> IPS, or inches per second, refers to the maximum velocity a mouse sensor supports. The higher the IPS, the faster you can move the mouse before it becomes incapable of tracking motions correctly.</p></li><li><p> Acceleration goes with IPS. In this context, it refers to how many Gs a mouse can withstand before it starts to track inaccurately.</p></li><li><p> Polling rate is a measure of how often a mouse tells a computer where it is. In general, the more frequently your mouse reports information to your PC, the more predictable its response time should be. Anything at 500Hz or above is fine for gaming. The current standard, and likely the sweet spot for most, is 1,000Hz. Many newer mice can go well beyond that, but the returns start to diminish unless you play on a monitor with a particularly high refresh rate.</p></li><li><p> Lift-off distance is the height at which a mouse&#39;s sensor stops tracking the surface below it. Many competitive players like this to be as low as possible in order to avoid unintended cursor movements while repositioning their mouse.</p></li></ul><h3> Software and onboard memory</h3><p> It doesn&#39;t take long to find horror stories about bugs and other niggling issues caused by gaming mouse software, so the ideal app is one that doesn&#39;t force you to use it all the time. It should let you adjust as many of the aspects above as possible, ideally to several distinct profiles. Preferably, you can save your settings directly to the mouse itself, letting you pick your customizations back up on another device without having to redownload any software. All this is most important on Windows, but Mac compatibility is always good to have, too.</p><h3> Warranty and customer support</h3><p> Most major gaming mice brands offer warranties between one and three years. The longer and more extensive a manufacturer&#39;s program is, the better. This is the case with most consumer tech, but we note it here because the gaming mouse market is particularly flush with products from less-than-household names, many of which you may see hyped up on YouTube, Reddit or elsewhere around the web. A bunch of these more obscure mice are genuinely great, but if you ever buy from a more niche brand, it&#39;s worth checking that some level of customer support is in place. We&#39;ve made sure our picks for the best gaming mice aren&#39;t riddled with an abnormal amount of poor user reviews.</p><h2> Best for most: Razer Basilisk V3 </h2><p><core-commerce id="5223710be61f4e24916286b1e372174a" data-type="product-list"></core-commerce></p><p> Of the gaming mice we tested, the <a data-i13n="cpos:5;pos:1;elm:affiliate_link;sellerN:Amazon;elmt:;" href="https://shopping.yahoo.com/rdlw?merchantId=66ea567a-c987-4c2e-a2ff-02904efde6ea&amp;siteId=us-engadget&amp;pageId=1p-autolink&amp;featureId=text-link&amp;merchantName=Amazon&amp;&amp;signature=AQAAAYNGujdFBAVEMm9foxZdG5eh7mFBxuoug4tm7vcbQRFk&amp;gcReferrer=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.amazon.com%2FRazer-Basilisk-Customizable-Ergonomic-Gaming%2Fdp%2FB09C13PZX7">Razer Basilisk V3</a> offers the most complete blend of price, performance, build quality and wide-ranging comfort. It&#39;s typically available between $50 and $70, and for that price it provides a sturdy body with a pleasingly textured matte finish and a shape that should be comfortable for each grip type and all but the smallest of hands. It uses durable optical switches, and its main buttons are large, relatively quiet and not fatiguing to press repeatedly.</p><p> The Basilisk V3 has a total of 11 customizable buttons, including two side buttons that are easy to reach but difficult to press by accident. There&#39;s a dedicated “sensitivity clutch” on the side as well, which lets you temporarily switch to a lower DPI for more precise aiming (though it&#39;s the one button that may be harder for smaller hands to reach without effort). Beneath those buttons is a well-sized thumb rest. The thumb wheel on top is loud and a bit clunky, but it can tilt left and right, and a built-in toggle lets it switch from ratcheted scrolling to a free-spin mode. That&#39;s great for navigating unwieldy documents.</p><p> At roughly 100 grams, the Basilisk V3 is on the heavier side for twitch shooters, but its PTFE feet let it glide with ease, and Razer&#39;s Focus+ sensor helps it track accurately. The weight shouldn&#39;t be a major hindrance unless you really take competitive FPS play seriously. (And if that&#39;s the case, see our premium recommendations below.) Either way, the included cable is impressively flexible, and the mouse&#39;s RGB lighting is fun without being garish. Razer&#39;s Synapse software is Windows-only and can be naggy with updates but makes it easy enough to set profiles and adjust DPI, polling rate, macros and RGB effects. You can also save up to five profiles to the mouse itself, though your lighting customizations won&#39;t carry over.</p><p> The Basilisk V3 is an ergonomic mouse designed for right-handed use. If you want an ambidextrous model with similar performance in the same price range, try the <a data-i13n="cpos:6;pos:1" href="https://shopping.yahoo.com/rdlw?merchantId=66ea567a-c987-4c2e-a2ff-02904efde6ea&amp;siteId=us-engadget&amp;pageId=1p-autolink&amp;featureId=text-link&amp;merchantName=Amazon&amp;&amp;signature=AQAAAZTd9cmXDEWeGbyDFOTX1aE-VaRE2U3ejbbiLu8ZXBZb&amp;gcReferrer=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.amazon.com%2FRazer-Viper-Ultralight-Ambidextrous-Gaming%2Fdp%2FB08QVM2JMQ&amp;uuid=XInL1Do73s1cqsp112459">Razer Viper 8KHz</a> . It ditches the multi-mode scroll wheel, and its ludicrously high max polling rate of 8,000Hz has little real-world benefit for most, but it&#39;s much lighter at 70g, and it has two customizable buttons on both its left and right sides. We&#39;ll also note the <a data-i13n="elm:affiliate_link;sellerN:Amazon;elmt:;cpos:7;pos:1" href="https://shopping.yahoo.com/rdlw?merchantId=66ea567a-c987-4c2e-a2ff-02904efde6ea&amp;siteId=us-engadget&amp;pageId=1p-autolink&amp;featureId=text-link&amp;merchantName=Amazon&amp;custData=eyJzb3VyY2VOYW1lIjoiV2ViLURlc2t0b3AtVmVyaXpvbiIsInN0b3JlSWQiOiI2NmVhNTY3YS1jOTg3LTRjMmUtYTJmZi0wMjkwNGVmZGU2ZWEiLCJsYW5kaW5nVXJsIjoiaHR0cHM6Ly93d3cuYW1hem9uLmNvbS9EZWF0aEFkZGVyLVdpcmVkLUdhbWluZy1Nb3VzZS1IeXBlclBvbGxpbmcvZHAvQjBCNlhUREpTMS8_dGFnPWdkZ3QwYy1wLW8ta3AtMjAiLCJjb250ZW50VXVpZCI6IjBhM2ViMjhlLTQ3MzAtNGFkNS1iNDA2LTI3ODMxYTcwZTBjYSJ9&amp;signature=AQAAATguD35-WbPLO5Z2tXEGS-mAMknZG1sWq6aVugpX9i70&amp;gcReferrer=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.amazon.com%2FDeathAdder-Wired-Gaming-Mouse-HyperPolling%2Fdp%2FB0B6XTDJS1%2F" class="rapid-with-clickid">Razer DeathAdder V3</a> , the wired version of our top wireless pick below, which is even lighter than the Viper 8KHz at 56g and should be better suited for righties solely focused on competitive gaming.</p><h2> Best premium: Razer DeathAdder V3 Pro </h2><p><core-commerce id="a72c3d16f26245d99dc7c715ea2c6860" data-type="product-list"></core-commerce></p><p> If money is no object, the best gaming mouse we tested is the <a data-i13n="cpos:8;pos:1" href="https://shopping.yahoo.com/rdlw?merchantId=66ea567a-c987-4c2e-a2ff-02904efde6ea&amp;siteId=us-engadget&amp;pageId=1p-autolink&amp;featureId=text-link&amp;merchantName=Amazon&amp;custData=eyJzb3VyY2VOYW1lIjoiV2ViLURlc2t0b3AtVmVyaXpvbiIsInN0b3JlSWQiOiI2NmVhNTY3YS1jOTg3LTRjMmUtYTJmZi0wMjkwNGVmZGU2ZWEiLCJsYW5kaW5nVXJsIjoiaHR0cHM6Ly93d3cuYW1hem9uLmNvbS9kcC9CMEI2WFpMTkhRP3RhZz1nZGd0MGMtcC1vLWtwLTIwIiwiY29udGVudFV1aWQiOiIwYTNlYjI4ZS00NzMwLTRhZDUtYjQwNi0yNzgzMWE3MGUwY2EifQ&amp;signature=AQAAAb1bJdIF2sbaMRXlFT9nEQcwwycTChYCrtFpNjG4yBA-&amp;gcReferrer=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.amazon.com%2Fdp%2FB0B6XZLNHQ&amp;uuid=dZolRyQnzKbtxi6x17460">Razer DeathAdder V3 Pro</a> . It&#39;s pricey at $150, but its superlight (63g) wireless design and top-notch sensor make it exceptionally responsive. While smaller-handed folks may find it a bit too tall, most should find its gently curved shape to be comfortable over long gaming sessions, regardless of their grip type. Its two side buttons are easy to reach and its body doesn&#39;t creak or flex. The scroll wheel is soft and quiet, while the main buttons feel satisfying but not overly sensitive. It also uses optical switches.</p><p> Battery life is rated at a decent 90 hours per charge, and you can connect an included (and highly flexible) USB-C cable in a pinch. Razer also sells a “ <a data-i13n="cpos:9;pos:1;elm:affiliate_link;sellerN:Razer Online Store;elmt:;" href="https://shopping.yahoo.com/rdlw?merchantId=358591a8-2981-451c-a839-e645b5522820&amp;siteId=us-engadget&amp;pageId=1p-autolink&amp;featureId=text-link&amp;merchantName=Razer+Online+Store&amp;&amp;signature=AQAAAVwwTPV2zdIL6TfbQU4E6P_r9lOjcbzHrt8yMkM8YruT&amp;gcReferrer=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.razer.com%2Fgaming-mice-accessories%2Frazer-hyperpolling-wireless-dongle">HyperPolling</a> ” dongle that increases the mouse&#39;s max polling rate to 4,000Hz, but few need that, and the company says using it can drop the mouse&#39;s battery life down to just 24 hours.</p><p> Despite its higher cost, the DeathAdder V3 Pro does forgo some of the Basilisk V3&#39;s extras: There&#39;s no RGB lighting, no Bluetooth, support for just one onboard profile and no free-spinning or side-tilting on the scroll wheel. The DPI switcher is inconveniently located on the bottom of the mouse, and there&#39;s no built-in storage compartment for the USB dongle.</p><p> Much of that helps the mouse trim the weight, however, and the whole point of the DeathAdder V3 Pro is to excel at the essentials – which it does. Razer&#39;s Focus Pro 30K sensor is complete overkill in terms of its maximum specs, but combined with the mouse&#39;s PTFE feet, low click latency and easy-to-flick design, it makes fast movements feel as “one-to-one” as any mouse we tested. If you&#39;re a competitive player who spends most of their time in twitchy FPS games, the DeathAdder V3 Pro should feel tailor-made to your priorities. That&#39;s really the main market here, though; most people don&#39;t need to drop $150 on this kind of device.</p><p> While its contours aren&#39;t as pronounced as the Basilisk V3, the DeathAdder V3 Pro is still designed for righties. For an ambidextrous model, <a data-i13n="cpos:10;pos:1" href="https://shopping.yahoo.com/rdlw?merchantId=66ea567a-c987-4c2e-a2ff-02904efde6ea&amp;siteId=us-engadget&amp;pageId=1p-autolink&amp;featureId=text-link&amp;merchantName=Amazon&amp;&amp;signature=AQAAAWMkEvdux1txSTRuTsKIZEHmlHlcaSQKzBDco6-_cQ1a&amp;gcReferrer=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.amazon.com%2FRazer-HyperSpeed-Wireless-Gaming-Mouse%2Fdp%2FB09VCR969M%3Fth%3D1&amp;uuid=qE7j30PdO1i6swFD19460">Razer&#39;s Viper V2 Pro</a> is really the “1B” option here, providing the same excellent performance in a flatter design that should play nicer with small hands and lefties. The <a data-i13n="cpos:11;pos:1" href="https://shopping.yahoo.com/rdlw?merchantId=66ea567a-c987-4c2e-a2ff-02904efde6ea&amp;siteId=us-engadget&amp;pageId=1p-autolink&amp;featureId=text-link&amp;merchantName=Amazon&amp;custData=eyJzb3VyY2VOYW1lIjoiV2ViLURlc2t0b3AtVmVyaXpvbiIsInN0b3JlSWQiOiI2NmVhNTY3YS1jOTg3LTRjMmUtYTJmZi0wMjkwNGVmZGU2ZWEiLCJsYW5kaW5nVXJsIjoiaHR0cHM6Ly93d3cuYW1hem9uLmNvbS9ncC9wcm9kdWN0L0IwQjZZM1hZRkc_dGFnPWdkZ3QwYy1wLW8ta3AtMjAiLCJjb250ZW50VXVpZCI6IjBhM2ViMjhlLTQ3MzAtNGFkNS1iNDA2LTI3ODMxYTcwZTBjYSJ9&amp;signature=AQAAAcplXxUbMYGzzS8lE2kXHMLdz8qIZqalIqny-uU49LUd&amp;gcReferrer=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.amazon.com%2Fgp%2Fproduct%2FB0B6Y3XYFG&amp;uuid=QFv5MreC4duaUSiz20460">Basilisk V3 Pro</a> , meanwhile, is essentially a wireless version of our “best for most” pick with the DeathAdder V3 Pro&#39;s upgraded sensor, though it&#39;s the heaviest option of this bunch at 112g. If comfort and features are more important to you than esports-style performance, it&#39;s a better buy, but since most people looking to buy a high-end wireless gaming mouse are especially fixated on competitive play, we gave the nod to the DeathAdder V3 Pro instead.</p><h2> Best budget: Logitech G203 Lightsync </h2><p><core-commerce id="b4e9dd37d3c44374914a2b1ab6a1550c" data-type="product-list"></core-commerce></p><p> If you just want a competent gaming mouse for as little money as possible, go with the <a data-i13n="cpos:12;pos:1;elm:affiliate_link;sellerN:Amazon;elmt:;" href="https://shopping.yahoo.com/rdlw?merchantId=66ea567a-c987-4c2e-a2ff-02904efde6ea&amp;siteId=us-engadget&amp;pageId=1p-autolink&amp;featureId=text-link&amp;merchantName=Amazon&amp;custData=eyJzb3VyY2VOYW1lIjoiV2ViLURlc2t0b3AtVmVyaXpvbiIsInN0b3JlSWQiOiI2NmVhNTY3YS1jOTg3LTRjMmUtYTJmZi0wMjkwNGVmZGU2ZWEiLCJsYW5kaW5nVXJsIjoiaHR0cHM6Ly93d3cuYW1hem9uLmNvbS9Mb2dpdGVjaC1MSUdIVFNZTkMtV2lyZWQtR2FtaW5nLU1vdXNlL2RwL0IwN1lOODJYM0I_dGg9MSZ0YWc9Z2RndDBjLXAtby1rcC0yMCIsImNvbnRlbnRVdWlkIjoiMGEzZWIyOGUtNDczMC00YWQ1LWI0MDYtMjc4MzFhNzBlMGNhIn0&amp;signature=AQAAAbes6LOKNznRedSWNs6AXj83OEdUK9jHcuCEtPbjBmzz&amp;gcReferrer=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.amazon.com%2FLogitech-LIGHTSYNC-Wired-Gaming-Mouse%2Fdp%2FB07YN82X3B%3Fth%3D1">Logitech G203 Lightsync</a> . Its design is likely too small and flat for palm-grippers with large hands, its scroll wheel feels somewhat mushy, and its rubbery cable isn&#39;t ideal. It uses mechanical switches, too. But the rest of it is smooth, reasonably light (85g) and sturdily built for the money, plus its shape plays well with fingertip or claw grips. It&#39;s also available in snazzy lilac and blue finishes alongside the usual black or white.</p><p> There are two customizable buttons on the right side – plus a DPI cycle button on top – but the G203&#39;s design is otherwise ambidextrous. The RGB lighting around the bottom of the device is tasteful, and Logitech&#39;s G Hub software makes it simple enough to tweak settings on both Windows and macOS. There&#39;s no onboard memory, however.</p><p> While the Logitech Mercury sensor within the G203 is a few years old and technically lacking compared to most newer alternatives, it&#39;s consistent and responsive enough to yield few complaints. The set of PTFE feet help, too. You wouldn&#39;t go out of your way to get the G203 to win competitive games of <em>Counter-Strike</em> , but it&#39;s perfectly fine for most games.</p><p> If you&#39;d prefer a cheap wireless gaming mouse, the <a data-i13n="cpos:13;pos:1" href="https://shopping.yahoo.com/rdlw?merchantId=66ea567a-c987-4c2e-a2ff-02904efde6ea&amp;siteId=us-engadget&amp;pageId=1p-autolink&amp;featureId=text-link&amp;merchantName=Amazon&amp;&amp;signature=AQAAAYf3W-S4Vvx_poFXUjQgQHIsSwEqIHylIVNzEzR4D4A-&amp;gcReferrer=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.amazon.com%2FLogitech-LIGHTSPEED-Wireless-Gaming-Mouse%2Fdp%2FB07CMS5Q6P&amp;uuid=V6zPpDeDxHOCxvX326460">Logitech&#39;s G305 Lightspeed</a> has more or less the same shape and build quality as the G203, but adds a more advanced sensor. Logitech says it can get up to 250 hours of battery life, but it requires a AA battery to work, which in turn pushes its weight to just over 100g.</p><h2> Best for MMOs: Logitech G600 </h2><p><core-commerce id="f467f3e367d841dc879ed15c28d16549" data-type="product-list"></core-commerce></p><p> If you want a mouse specifically designed for MMO games, get the <a data-i13n="cpos:14;pos:1;elm:affiliate_link;sellerN:Amazon;elmt:;" href="https://shopping.yahoo.com/rdlw?merchantId=66ea567a-c987-4c2e-a2ff-02904efde6ea&amp;siteId=us-engadget&amp;pageId=1p-autolink&amp;featureId=text-link&amp;merchantName=Amazon&amp;&amp;signature=AQAAAVz0MS7oumMMOb25NYnt1CQSvgZr_NEfB5Op5dXAAIcn&amp;gcReferrer=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.amazon.com%2FLogitech-Gaming-Backlit-Programmable-Buttons%2Fdp%2FB0086UK7IQ">Logitech G600</a> . It&#39;s ancient, having launched <a data-i13n="cpos:15;pos:1" href="https://www.engadget.com/2012-06-14-logitech-g600-mouse-targets-button-craving-mmo-gamers.html">way back in 2012</a> , and as such it uses mechanical switches and a laser sensor (the Avago S9808) that can be less precise than a more modern optical sensor. It&#39;s hefty at 133g, and it has a wide body that&#39;s not ideal for small hands or fingertip grips. Plus, its cable isn&#39;t particularly flexible, and its scroll wheel and main buttons are just <em>OK</em> .</p><p> Hear us out, though. The G600 is far from the only mouse in this style to be on the larger side, and any performance shortcomings it may have will be difficult to notice in an MMO. Outside of faster action games, it tracks fine. For large and average hands, particularly those that use a palm grip, the G600&#39;s sloped shape should be comfortable. Plus, the scroll wheel can tilt left and right.</p><p> The most important thing an MMO mouse can do is let you access several in-game commands with minimal effort. The G600 does that, supplying 12 customizable side buttons that are angled in a way that distinguishes them without constantly forcing you to look down. Few MMO mice make these buttons “easy to reach,” but the G600 does about as well as one can.</p><p> The mouse&#39;s killer feature, however, is a third click button, which sits under your ring finger and brings up an entire second set of commands when pressed. This means you can access up to <em>24</em> different inputs with just one hand, which is a godsend in MMOs that ask you to juggle multiple hotbars&#39; worth of commands. Being able to get through your “rotations” in a game like <em>Final Fantasy XIV</em> without having to contort your fingers around the keyboard is hugely convenient. This feature isn&#39;t exclusive to the G600, but it&#39;s not commonplace either. Best of all, this mouse is affordable, typically retailing around $35. There are certainly <em>nicer</em> MMO mice available, but the G600&#39;s functionality is enough to make it the best value in its market.</p><h2> Other honorable mentions </h2><figure><img src="https://s.yimg.com/os/creatr-uploaded-images/2023-02/0afb9330-a984-11ed-8fc1-932404a51991" alt="A white gaming mouse called the Ninjutso Sora rested on top of a black mouse pad on a desk." data-uuid="dc53e14b-ca28-3fc9-8fa4-1c3f75ce3fc0"><figcaption></figcaption><div class="photo-credit"> Photo by Jeff Dunn / Engadget</div></figure><p> If you don&#39;t like the Razer aesthetic, <a data-i13n="cpos:16;pos:1" href="https://shopping.yahoo.com/rdlw?merchantId=66ea567a-c987-4c2e-a2ff-02904efde6ea&amp;siteId=us-engadget&amp;pageId=1p-autolink&amp;featureId=text-link&amp;merchantName=Amazon&amp;custData=eyJzb3VyY2VOYW1lIjoiV2ViLURlc2t0b3AtVmVyaXpvbiIsInN0b3JlSWQiOiI2NmVhNTY3YS1jOTg3LTRjMmUtYTJmZi0wMjkwNGVmZGU2ZWEiLCJsYW5kaW5nVXJsIjoiaHR0cHM6Ly93d3cuYW1hem9uLmNvbS9Mb2dpdGVjaC1TVVBFUkxJR0hULVVsdHJhLUxpZ2h0d2VpZ2h0LVByb2dyYW1tYWJsZS1Db21wYXRpYmxlL2RwL0IwODdMWENURko_dGFnPWdkZ3QwYy1wLW8ta3AtMjAiLCJjb250ZW50VXVpZCI6IjBhM2ViMjhlLTQ3MzAtNGFkNS1iNDA2LTI3ODMxYTcwZTBjYSJ9&amp;signature=AQAAAUxRbFoQnyfwqqGQ3fEX1XnUs1PwuV1-2lnU54hYQOw0&amp;gcReferrer=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.amazon.com%2FLogitech-SUPERLIGHT-Ultra-Lightweight-Programmable-Compatible%2Fdp%2FB087LXCTFJ&amp;uuid=eli55SVFd8FYAgsQ21460">Logitech&#39;s G Pro X Superlight</a> is a close runner-up to the DeathAdder V3 Pro whose <a data-i13n="cpos:17;pos:1" href="https://www.engadget.com/logitech-g-pro-x-superlight-mouse-irl-140037783.html">praises we&#39;ve sung</a> in the past. If you see it for less than the Razer models or just want a high-performing mouse for Mac, it&#39;s great, but note that it has a lower battery life rating (70 hrs) and charges over microUSB instead of USB-C. It&#39;s also a few years old, so we wouldn&#39;t be surprised to see an updated model in the coming months.</p><p> The <a data-i13n="cpos:18;pos:1" href="https://shopping.yahoo.com/rdlw?merchantId=66ea567a-c987-4c2e-a2ff-02904efde6ea&amp;siteId=us-engadget&amp;pageId=1p-autolink&amp;featureId=text-link&amp;merchantName=Amazon&amp;custData=eyJzb3VyY2VOYW1lIjoiV2ViLURlc2t0b3AtVmVyaXpvbiIsInN0b3JlSWQiOiI2NmVhNTY3YS1jOTg3LTRjMmUtYTJmZi0wMjkwNGVmZGU2ZWEiLCJsYW5kaW5nVXJsIjoiaHR0cHM6Ly93d3cuYW1hem9uLmNvbS9ncC9wcm9kdWN0L0IwODJMUk1ZNTM_dGFnPWdkZ3QwYy1wLW8ta3AtMjAiLCJjb250ZW50VXVpZCI6IjBhM2ViMjhlLTQ3MzAtNGFkNS1iNDA2LTI3ODMxYTcwZTBjYSJ9&amp;signature=AQAAAXFmNxidvZLA2UOMdo60bwleREGcJYUGfDFFS1r62wic&amp;gcReferrer=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.amazon.com%2Fgp%2Fproduct%2FB082LRMY53&amp;uuid=wuBGOnxpOC6OpU8N31461">Corsair Scimitar RGB Elite</a> is a better-built alternative to the G600 with a more modern optical sensor. It lacks the G600&#39;s third main button, but it&#39;s a good buy if you don&#39;t need that and see it on sale.</p><p> The <a data-i13n="elm:affiliate_link;sellerN:Razer;elmt:;cpos:19;pos:1" href="https://shopping.yahoo.com/rdlw?merchantId=d043077a-4ba1-4321-a933-30b8701d8d31&amp;siteId=us-engadget&amp;pageId=1p-autolink&amp;featureId=text-link&amp;merchantName=Razer&amp;&amp;signature=AQAAAaIW2LNaI1Ncz3p5KTe05-PWadEvZYqeRzsswzsw2mFC&amp;gcReferrer=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.razer.com%2Fgaming-mice%2Frazer-naga-left-handed-edition%2FRZ01-03410100-R3M1" class="rapid-with-clickid">Razer Naga Left-Handed Edition</a> isn&#39;t nearly as good of a value as the G600 or Scimitar RGB Elite, but it&#39;s one of the few MMO mice that&#39;s actually built for lefties.</p><p> The <a data-i13n="cpos:20;pos:1" href="https://ninjutso.com/products/ninjutso-sora-wireless-gaming-mouse">Ninjutso Sora</a> comes from a lesser-known brand and is harder to actually purchase as of this writing, but it looks and performs like a G Pro X Superlight for smaller hands. Its main buttons are fairly stiff, but it&#39;s incredibly light at 45g, so it plays great for FPS games.</p><p> It&#39;s a close call between the <a data-i13n="elm:affiliate_link;sellerN:Amazon;elmt:;cpos:21;pos:1" href="https://shopping.yahoo.com/rdlw?merchantId=66ea567a-c987-4c2e-a2ff-02904efde6ea&amp;siteId=us-engadget&amp;pageId=1p-autolink&amp;featureId=text-link&amp;merchantName=Amazon&amp;custData=eyJzb3VyY2VOYW1lIjoiV2ViLURlc2t0b3AtVmVyaXpvbiIsInN0b3JlSWQiOiI2NmVhNTY3YS1jOTg3LTRjMmUtYTJmZi0wMjkwNGVmZGU2ZWEiLCJsYW5kaW5nVXJsIjoiaHR0cHM6Ly93d3cuYW1hem9uLmNvbS9kcC9CMEJYNTJQQ0o1P3RhZz1nZGd0MGMtcC1vLWtwLTIwIiwiY29udGVudFV1aWQiOiIwYTNlYjI4ZS00NzMwLTRhZDUtYjQwNi0yNzgzMWE3MGUwY2EifQ&amp;signature=AQAAAVXQTMlXzhtn1Rpv0m92LQMdLDnMBUTFraYiljJn3XyX&amp;gcReferrer=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.amazon.com%2Fdp%2FB0BX52PCJ5" data-demonetize-referrer="https://www.amazon.com/dp/B0BX52PCJ5?th=1" class="rapid-with-clickid">HyperX Pulsefire Haste 2</a> and the Razer Viper 8KHz for those who prefer an ambidextrous, mostly flat shape. Both perform well for competitive play, but the Pulsefire Haste 2 is significantly lighter at 53g, thanks to a clever design with cutouts on the bottom that are covered by the mouse&#39;s label. That said, it has two fewer side buttons, and it doesn&#39;t support more than one onboard storage profile. As we write this, you can also find the Viper 8KHz for $10 less. If that ever changes, though, or if the lower weight is just more important to you, the Pulsefire Haste 2 is a great wired option. </p><figure><img src="https://s.yimg.com/os/creatr-uploaded-images/2023-08/ee9371b0-3b8a-11ee-bee7-467a89a03759" style="height:1200px;width:2000px;" alt="A few of the gaming mice we tested for our latest update. Left to right: the Glorious Model I 2 Wireless, the Razer Cobra Pro, the Razer Basilisk V3 X HyperSpeed and the HyperX Pulsefire Haste 2." data-uuid="07799df9-24e7-3eb9-b759-a0317c1772e3"><figcaption></figcaption><div class="photo-credit"> Photo by Jeff Dunn / Engadget</div></figure><p> The <a data-i13n="cpos:22;pos:1" href="https://lamzu.com/products/lamzu-atlantis-og-v2">Lamzu Atlantis OG V2</a> is another fine choice for FPS games with snappy performance and a symmetrical, ultralight (55g) build that&#39;s particularly well-suited to claw grips. Its bottom plate has a semi-open design, however, so it&#39;s at least somewhat more susceptible to damage from dust and debris than our picks above. As of this writing, it&#39;s also difficult to find in stock.</p><p> The <a data-i13n="elm:affiliate_link;sellerN:Amazon;elmt:;cpos:23;pos:1" href="https://shopping.yahoo.com/rdlw?merchantId=66ea567a-c987-4c2e-a2ff-02904efde6ea&amp;siteId=us-engadget&amp;pageId=1p-autolink&amp;featureId=text-link&amp;merchantName=Amazon&amp;&amp;signature=AQAAAYQuGsHVE7TWICKD1qrHfkCVLdmRBUHg8RnvcUJQ2ds7&amp;gcReferrer=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.amazon.com%2FRazer-Cobra-Wired-Gaming-Mouse%2Fdp%2FB0C51J2ZXN" class="rapid-with-clickid">Razer Cobra</a> has a similarly compact shape as the Logitech G203, with a much lower weight (58g), a more flexible cable and optical switches. It&#39;s priced at $40, putting it in something of a no man&#39;s land between the G203&#39;s and Basilisk V3&#39;s typical street prices, but it should be an upgrade over the G203 if it&#39;s still within your budget and you need something small.</p><p> There&#39;s plenty to like about the <a data-i13n="elm:affiliate_link;sellerN:Amazon;elmt:;cpos:24;pos:1" href="https://shopping.yahoo.com/rdlw?merchantId=66ea567a-c987-4c2e-a2ff-02904efde6ea&amp;siteId=us-engadget&amp;pageId=1p-autolink&amp;featureId=text-link&amp;merchantName=Amazon&amp;&amp;signature=AQAAAeGQ2DPKO97USQhz163YcJdvtW2lsmj1RiI_X_Z1uQWQ&amp;gcReferrer=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.amazon.com%2FGlorious-Model-Wireless-Matte-White%2Fdp%2FB0BLFB5RRD%2F" data-demonetize-referrer="https://www.amazon.com/Glorious-Model-Wireless-Matte-White/dp/B0BLFB5RRD/?th=1" class="rapid-with-clickid">Glorious Model I 2 Wireless</a> : an ergonomically-friendly shape that&#39;s reminiscent of the Basilisk V3/Logitech G502 X but lighter at 75g, four customizable side buttons, the ability to connect over a USB receiver or Bluetooth, a smooth scroll wheel and tasteful RGB lighting, all for $100. However, its honeycomb-style design and mechanical switches both raise concerns about its long-term durability.</p><p> The <a data-i13n="elm:affiliate_link;sellerN:Amazon;elmt:;cpos:25;pos:1" href="https://shopping.yahoo.com/rdlw?merchantId=66ea567a-c987-4c2e-a2ff-02904efde6ea&amp;siteId=us-engadget&amp;pageId=1p-autolink&amp;featureId=text-link&amp;merchantName=Amazon&amp;&amp;signature=AQAAASe_oWMZuAK3OBU9VFvyFLKCWoYnHkwceibrzrG1L3U_&amp;gcReferrer=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.amazon.com%2FRazer-Basilisk-HyperSpeed-Customizable-Wireless%2Fdp%2FB0BXBC26X8" data-demonetize-referrer="https://www.amazon.com/Razer-Basilisk-HyperSpeed-Customizable-Wireless/dp/B0BXBC26X8?th=1" class="rapid-with-clickid">Razer Basilisk V3 X HyperSpeed</a> is a more affordable wireless version of the Basilisk V3 with the same comfortable shape and layout, plus a quieter scroll wheel. Because it requires a AA battery for power, though, it weighs around 115g, which isn&#39;t great for fast-paced games. The scroll wheel can&#39;t tilt left or right, either, nor can it switch between a ratcheted and free-spin mode. It also uses less durable mechanical switches and only supports one onboard profile. Still, it&#39;s a decent value at $70.</p><p> The <a data-i13n="cpos:26;pos:1" href="https://shopping.yahoo.com/rdlw?merchantId=66ea567a-c987-4c2e-a2ff-02904efde6ea&amp;siteId=us-engadget&amp;pageId=1p-autolink&amp;featureId=text-link&amp;merchantName=Amazon&amp;custData=eyJzb3VyY2VOYW1lIjoiV2ViLURlc2t0b3AtVmVyaXpvbiIsInN0b3JlSWQiOiI2NmVhNTY3YS1jOTg3LTRjMmUtYTJmZi0wMjkwNGVmZGU2ZWEiLCJsYW5kaW5nVXJsIjoiaHR0cHM6Ly93d3cuYW1hem9uLmNvbS9kcC9CMDk2WEtKSzFWP3RhZz1nZGd0MGMtcC1vLWtwLTIwIiwiY29udGVudFV1aWQiOiIwYTNlYjI4ZS00NzMwLTRhZDUtYjQwNi0yNzgzMWE3MGUwY2EifQ&amp;signature=AQAAARduMkMj5jWARKv2RRCmbMckE8DSxvxVVmJSIn_W7XSs&amp;gcReferrer=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.amazon.com%2Fdp%2FB096XKJK1V">Asus ROG Gladius III</a> doesn&#39;t stand out from our main recommendations in terms of design or performance, and its software can be buggy, but it&#39;s unusually <a data-i13n="cpos:27;pos:1" href="https://rog.asus.com/articles/gaming-keyboards-gaming-mice/guide-how-to-replace-the-switches-in-your-rog-gladius-iii-gaming-mouse/">easy to repair</a> . That <a data-i13n="cpos:28;pos:1" href="https://www.ifixit.com/News/57357/more-pc-gaming-mice-should-follow-rogs-repairable-switches">is admirable</a> and should make the mouse a good long-term investment for DIY types.</p> This article originally appeared on Engadget at https://www.engadget.com/best-gaming-mouse-140004638.html?src=rss]]>; </description><link/><![CDATA[https://www.engadget.com/best-gaming-mouse-140004638.html?src=rss]]><source_id> engadget_479</source_id><guid ispermalink="false"> 0a3eb28e-4730-4ad5-b406-27831a70e0ca</guid><dc:creator> Jeff Dunn</dc:creator><source/><![CDATA[Engadget]]><dc:publisher>恩杰特</dc:publisher><dc:rightsholder>恩杰特</dc:rightsholder><pubDate>Tue, 15 Aug 2023 16:10:04 +0000</pubDate><ingested> 1692118659</ingested><modified> 2023-08-15T16:57:52+00:00 </modified><category><![CDATA[Computing]]></category><category><![CDATA[Shopping]]></category><category><![CDATA[Technology & Electronics]]></category><category><![CDATA[Electronics Accessories]]></category><category><![CDATA[Hobbies & Personal Activities]]></category><category><![CDATA[site|engadget]]></category><category><![CDATA[provider_name|Engadget]]></category><category><![CDATA[region|US]]></category><category><![CDATA[language|en-US]]></category><category><![CDATA[author_name|Jeff Dunn]]></category><media:content height="1200" medium="image" url="https://s.yimg.com/os/creatr-uploaded-images/2023-02/a4d5a1a0-a982-11ed-beef-dc6309a69735" width="2000"><media:keywords> headline </media:keywords><media:media_html><![CDATA[ ]]></media:media_html><dc:identifier><![CDATA[1]]></dc:identifier><media:credit><![CDATA[ ]]></media:credit><media:description><![CDATA[ ]]></media:description><media:title><![CDATA[ ]]></media:title></media:content><media:content height="1200" medium="image" url="https://media-mbst-pub-ue1.s3.amazonaws.com/creatr-uploaded-images/2023-02/a4d5a1a0-a982-11ed-beef-dc6309a69735" width="2000"><media:media_html><![CDATA[ ]]></media:media_html><dc:identifier><![CDATA[2]]></dc:identifier><media:credit><![CDATA[Jeff Dunn / Engadget]]></media:credit><media:description><![CDATA[A collection of the gaming mice we tested for our buying guide, neatly laid out on a brown wooden table.]]></media:description><media:title><![CDATA[Gaming mice buying guide]]></media:title></media:content></item><item><title><![CDATA[YouTube Music debuts Samples, a TikTok-style feed for music discovery]]></title><description type="html"><![CDATA[<p>在过去的几年里，基本上每个重要的平台都对 TikTok 标志性的垂直视频滚动提要做出了自己的贡献。 YouTube Music 是最新的。 Today, the app will get a <a data-i13n="cpos:1;pos:1" href="https://blog.youtube/news-and-events/taking-music-discovery-to-the-next-level-with-samples/">vertical video feed called Samples</a> that YouTube describes as a one-tap way to quickly sample and find new music.</p><p>示例位于应用程序底部的一个新选项卡中，旁边是主页源、您的图书馆和探索部分。点按“样本”会自动启动 YouTube Music 认为您会喜欢的歌曲的垂直短视频剪辑。当然，它会根据您的品味概况来提取歌曲，重点是您喜欢的艺术家以及您以前可能没有听过的相关艺术家。</p><span id="end-legacy-contents"></span><p>该应用程序已经有多个播放列表，可以根据您的收听习惯进行调整，其中包括一个 Supermix，可以将歌曲和艺术家汇集到您所有的收听习惯中。还有一个“发现”播放列表，自然地，重点关注您不熟悉但根据您的历史记录可能喜欢的内容。 YouTube Music 产品经理 Gregor Dodson 告诉 Engadget，Samples feed 的算法与这两者都有些不同——它试图在两个播放列表之间定位，突出显示你可能熟悉的艺术家，但提取你没有看过的剪辑前。</p><p>您将在样本中看到的剪辑只有 30 秒长，但这足以让您对歌曲有一定的了解。如果这不是您要找的歌曲，只需向上滑动，您就会跳到另一首歌曲，并且您可以随心所欲地执行此操作。 Spotify 最近<a data-i13n="cpos:2;pos:1" href="https://www.engadget.com/spotify-debuts-its-tiktok-style-music-discovery-feed-183359654.html">添加了自己的垂直视频源</a>，但这并不是为了发现，更多的是提供一种快速滚动播放列表中歌曲预览的方法。但随着 Spotify 和 YouTube Music 都实施了这样的新功能，我们很快就会看到更多应用程序也这样做。</p><p>在 Samples 推出之前，我尝试了几天，我发现最有趣的是用它作为更长聆听会话的起点，Dodson 证实这是设计使然。 “短视频[和]无限滚动在音乐发现方面有着非常有趣的应用，”他说。 “这是发现新音乐的简单方法，但这并不是旅程的终点​​——这只是寻找新艺术家或歌曲的开始。” </p><figure><img src="https://s.yimg.com/os/creatr-uploaded-images/2023-08/2143b520-3b72-11ee-af7f-eb1978592b07" style="height:1292px;width:1634px;" alt="YouTube 音乐样本" data-uuid="ea40296b-1045-31d2-9963-b4393bdd2c80"><figcaption></figcaption><div class="photo-credit"> YouTube</div></figure><p>为此，示例视频视图上覆盖了许多控件。在任何样本中，您都可以点击“竖起大拇指”将歌曲保存到“喜欢的歌曲”播放列表中。您还可以将歌曲保存到您创建的任何播放列表中。在这两个选项之间，可以很容易地快速扫描样本并保存一堆歌曲以进一步检查。如果您听到想要立即完整播放的内容，只需点击屏幕一角的旧播放按钮即可。</p><p>由于我们谈论的是 YouTube，因此还有一个“Shorts”按钮可让您进入 YouTube 主应用程序。它会向您显示使用您选择的音频创建的其他 Shorts 剪辑，并让您开始使用该歌曲制作自己的剪辑。最后，共享按钮的功能正是您所想的 - 您会得到一个链接，可以进入许多其他应用程序，例如消息、Reddit、Facebook 以及您可能安装的其他应用程序。</p><p>在溢出菜单中，您可以找到很多其他选项，例如从歌曲开始连续广播电台、跳到艺术家页面以查找更多音乐、将曲目保存到您的库等等。我的“开始广播”按钮在样本视频中更加突出，因为我发现这是跳入一组自动生成的曲调的好方法，其氛围与最初引起我注意的样本相同（并且耳朵）。</p><p>我对示例的主要问题是用户界面之一。具体来说，当您切换视图时，并不总是清楚您最终会进入应用程序的哪个位置。点击“示例”选项卡将启动视频滚动，要退出视频滚动，您可以点击其他底部导航选项卡之一；点击“播放”按钮将打开熟悉的 YouTube 音乐播放器控件。最后，向下滑动以隐藏播放器界面，您将返回到示例。看起来很清楚。但有一次，我按下播放按钮来听一首歌，然后将手机旋转到横向以全屏观看视频。当下一首歌曲开始时，我将手机旋转回横向，应用程序立即将我带回样本视图，我已经听过的歌曲片段仍在播放。</p><p>还有一次，我开始播放一首歌曲，然后点击“正在播放”屏幕顶部的开关来关闭视频，然后只听这首歌。我从自动生成的类似音乐电台中又听了几首歌曲，然后向下滑动以隐藏“正在播放”用户界面并浏览应用程序。我再次被扔回样本视图。这确实具有一定的逻辑意义，因为这就是整个聆听体验的开始。但我已经习惯了隐藏“正在播放”屏幕并在播放音乐的同时浏览应用程序，这有点不和谐。也就是说，我可以点击底部的“主页”选项卡并继续我正在播放的内容。它有效，但添加示例确实改变了应用程序的一些预期行为。</p><p>抛开这些争论不谈，Samples 似乎是 YouTube Music 应用的一个非常方便的补充。在我测试它的几天里，它一直提供我喜欢的艺术家的音乐，而且歌曲选择确实是我平时不太熟悉的东西。它的视频剪辑方面对我来说并不重要，但考虑到如今有多少艺术家正在制作出色的视频，记住这些视觉效果有时值得一看是很有趣的。 （感谢 YouTube Music 提供了<a data-i13n="cpos:3;pos:1" href="https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=WJ9-xN6dCW4">Phoebe Bridgers 的《I Know the End》狂野视频</a>。）更重要的是，它确实可以作为一个起点，让我深入挖掘一些我已经忘记的艺术家，或者找到一首适合的曲子。设置播放列表或电台的基调。</p><p> YouTube 表示，示例功能将从今天开始在全球范围内向 Android 和 iOS 用户推出。与大多数新功能一样，它可能不会立即影响您的应用程序，因此您可能需要有点耐心。</p> This article originally appeared on Engadget at https://www.engadget.com/youtube-music-debuts-samples-a-tiktok-style-feed-for-music-discovery-160007555.html?src=rss]]>; </description><link/><![CDATA[https://www.engadget.com/youtube-music-debuts-samples-a-tiktok-style-feed-for-music-discovery-160007555.html?src=rss]]><source_id> engadget_479</source_id><guid ispermalink="false"> c398b21a-0b56-44de-bb22-6722dba5de8e</guid><dc:creator> Nathan Ingraham</dc:creator><source/><![CDATA[Engadget]]><dc:publisher>恩杰特</dc:publisher><dc:rightsholder>恩杰特</dc:rightsholder><pubDate>Tue, 15 Aug 2023 16:00:07 +0000</pubDate><ingested> 1692122101</ingested><modified> 2023-08-15T17:55:08+00:00</modified><category><![CDATA[Software]]></category><category><![CDATA[Music]]></category><category><![CDATA[Media]]></category><category><![CDATA[Arts & Entertainment]]></category><category><![CDATA[site|engadget]]></category><category><![CDATA[provider_name|Engadget]]></category><category><![CDATA[region|US]]></category><category><![CDATA[language|en-US]]></category><category><![CDATA[author_name|Nathan Ingraham]]></category><media:content height="1600" medium="image" url="https://s.yimg.com/os/creatr-uploaded-images/2023-08/1cfb47f0-3b70-11ee-bcfb-1da6ab799bdf" width="2400"><media:keywords> headline </media:keywords><media:media_html><![CDATA[ ]]></media:media_html><dc:identifier><![CDATA[1]]></dc:identifier><media:credit><![CDATA[ ]]></media:credit><media:description><![CDATA[ ]]></media:description><media:title><![CDATA[ ]]></media:title></media:content><media:content height="1600" medium="image" url="https://media-mbst-pub-ue1.s3.amazonaws.com/creatr-uploaded-images/2023-08/1cfb47f0-3b70-11ee-bcfb-1da6ab799bdf" width="2400"><media:media_html><![CDATA[ ]]></media:media_html><dc:identifier><![CDATA[2]]></dc:identifier><media:credit><![CDATA[Photo by Nathan Ingraham / Engadget]]></media:credit><media:description><![CDATA[YouTube Music Samples]]></media:description><media:title><![CDATA[YouTube Music Samples]]></media:title></media:content></item><item><title><![CDATA[Google's latest AI trick is summarizing long web pages]]></title><description type="html"><![CDATA[<p>谷歌正在测试其搜索中的生成式人工智能的新功能，这将使其成为<a data-i13n="cpos:1;pos:1" href="https://www.engadget.com/microsoft-new-bing-edge-ai-copilot-hands-on-demo-test-chatgpt-openai-213332455.html">微软 Edge 中的 AI Copilot</a>更名副其实的竞争对手。这家科技巨头已经启动了一项早期实验，旨在突破搜索本身，打造人工智能驱动的生成式搜索体验 (SGE)。该功能被称为“浏览时 SGE”，可以快速生成网络上长格式内容的最显着点。这家科技巨头将其定位为一种工具，可以用来更轻松地消化可能需要广泛研究的复杂主题。但是，该工具将无法为付费文章提供要点，只能为您可以免费查看的某些网页提供要点。</p><p>每当 Google 的 AI 可以为您正在访问的页面生成关键点时，您都​​会在移动设备屏幕底部或桌面侧边栏中看到一个选项，显示“获取 AI 生成的关键点”。每个关键点都直接链接到它所引用的页面部分，因此您可以立即跳转到它。还有一个“浏览页面”部分，显示文章回答的问题。目前，该功能仅在 Android 和 iOS 上的 Google 应用程序中可用，但在接下来的几天内将在桌面版 Chrome 上推出。如果您已选择试用 SGE，该工具会自动打开，但您也可以在<a data-i13n="cpos:2;pos:1" href="https://labs.google.com/">搜索实验室</a>中将其作为独立实验打开。与任何其他实验一样，它可能会随着时间的推移而发展，具体取决于测试人员的反馈。 </p><span id="end-legacy-contents"></span><figure><img src="https://s.yimg.com/os/creatr-uploaded-images/2023-08/96952c60-3b5d-11ee-bf9f-03085f94d5cc" style="height:739px;width:800px;" alt="谷歌人工智能生成的关键点功能在移动设备上的屏幕截图。" data-uuid="3fd779a7-76b1-3c50-8bd5-e9638829b985"><figcaption></figcaption><div class="photo-credit">谷歌</div></figure><p>Google 还将很快推出一项新功能，可以帮助您更好地熟悉与 STEM、经济、历史和其他主题相关的新概念和术语。更准确地说，它正在改进人工智能生成的对这些主题的响应，这样当您将鼠标悬停在某些单词上时，您将看到定义和相关图表或图像的预览。它可以为您提供一种快速的方法来理解人工智能对您的问题的答案，而无需深入研究您不熟悉的所有概念。</p><p>最后，如果你是一名程序员，不反对使用 AI 工具进行编码，Google 还为 SGE 添加了新功能，可以帮助你更好地理解和调试它生成的代码。从今天开始，关键字、注释和字符串等元素将在概述中的代码段中进行颜色编码和突出显示，以便您可以快速解析人工智能的输出并确定它是否会按预期工作。</p> This article originally appeared on Engadget at https://www.engadget.com/googles-latest-ai-trick-is-summarizing-long-web-pages-160004700.html?src=rss]]>; </description><link/><![CDATA[https://www.engadget.com/googles-latest-ai-trick-is-summarizing-long-web-pages-160004700.html?src=rss]]><source_id> engadget_479</source_id><guid ispermalink="false"> 26b64e9e-42c2-447c-83b2-3ecbde782cd5</guid><dc:creator> Mariella Moon</dc:creator><source/><![CDATA[Engadget]]><dc:publisher>恩杰特</dc:publisher><dc:rightsholder>恩杰特</dc:rightsholder><pubDate>Tue, 15 Aug 2023 16:00:04 +0000</pubDate><ingested> 1692100270</ingested><modified> 2023-08-15T11:51:14+00:00 </modified><category><![CDATA[Technology & Electronics]]></category><category><![CDATA[site|engadget]]></category><category><![CDATA[provider_name|Engadget]]></category><category><![CDATA[region|US]]></category><category><![CDATA[language|en-US]]></category><catego